Ausführliche Beschreibung

Noch zu erledigen:
Rewrite shape classes to use GUI-references. In order to do that, a special reference counting function should be provided that use the non-GUI counter.

548  wxFFile file(MurFileData.name.GetFullPath(), _T("w"));
549 
550  if (!file.IsOpened()) {
551  wxLogError(_("Cannot open routes file '%s' for writing."),
552  MurFileData.name.GetFullPath().c_str());
553  return;
554  }
555 
556  std::string RouteConfig;
557 
558  compat30::SaveRoutes(RouteConfig);
559 
560  wxMBConv &converter = MurFileData.type == MutFileDataType::UTF8TextRoute ?
561  (wxMBConv&)wxConvUTF8 : (wxMBConv&)wxConvISO8859_1;
562 
563  if (file.Write(_T("# Mutabor 3.x routes configuration\n"),
564  converter))
565  if (file.Write(RouteConfig, converter)) {
566  file.Close();
567  return;
568  }
569 
570  wxLogError(_("Error writing file '%s'."),
571  MurFileData.name.GetFullPath().c_str());
572  file.Close();
573  }
574  break;
575  case MutFileDataType::XMLRoute1: {
576  xmltree document(_T("mutabor-routes"),true);
577  mutabor::RouteFactory::SaveRoutes(document);
578  document.Save(MurFileData.name.GetFullPath());
579 
580  }
581  break;
582  case MutFileDataType::Canceled:
583  case MutFileDataType::Unknown:
584  case MutFileDataType::LogicSource:
585  UNREACHABLE;
586  return;
587  }
588 }

template<class T >
void mutaborGUI::MutDeviceShape< T >::DoLeftDblClick ( )
protectedvirtual

Execute the double click.

Despite its name this function must not be called directly from a double click event handler. Click event handlers are not proof against control deletion.

424  devicetype dev =
425  DeviceFactory::Create<devicetype>(type);
426  if (dev) {
427  TRACEC;
428  thistype * newdev =
429  GUIDeviceFactory::CreateShape (dev,
430  GetParent());
431 
432  if (! newdev) {
433  UNREACHABLEC;
434  return;
435  }
436  mutASSERT(newdev->device);
437  TRACEC;
438  newdev -> readDialog (dlg);
439  if (LogicOn && !(newdev->device->IsOpen()))
440  newdev->device->Open();
441 
442  TRACEC;
443  destroySelf = replaceSelfBy (newdev);
444  }
445  }
446  } else if (Res == ::wxID_REMOVE) {
447  TRACEC;
448  device -> Destroy();
449  }
450 
451  // Now, we may be deleted.
452 
453  dlg->Destroy();
454  DebugCheckRoutes();
455  TRACEC;
456 
457  if (Res != ::wxID_REMOVE && !destroySelf) {
458  Layout();
459  InvalidateBestSize();
460  Fit();
461  Refresh();
462  }
463  if (parent) {
464  parent->InvalidateBestSize();
465  parent->Layout();
466  parent->FitInside();
467  parent->Refresh();
468  parent->Update();
469  } else if (Res != ::wxID_REMOVE && !destroySelf) Update();
470  /* we don't need to destroy this control.
471  This should have been done during device destruction
472  */
473  TRACE;
474  }

wxPanel * mutaborGUI::MutInputMidiFileDeviceShape::GetFilterPanel ( wxWindow *  parent,
mutabor::Route &  route 
) const
virtual

transfers the configuration data of an input filter from a route object to a dialog panel.

Filter data is currently stored in some variables of the route class. These variables are reused for several purposes. depending on the corresponding input device..

This function creates an input filter panel for a route dialog and initializes it with the appropriate values of the route as they are inerpred by a MIDI file input device class.

Parameter
parentParent window of the panel (usually a dialog or panel)
routeRoute to read the data from
Rückgabe
A panel, that is correctly initialized to communicate the filter data with the user. The calling function must take care of it's deletion (or delegate it)

93  if (!panel) return NULL;
94  InputMidiFile * dev = dynamic_cast<InputMidiFile *> (device.get());
95  const int maxchannel = dev?dev->GetMaxChannel():maxint;
96  const int minchannel = dev?dev->GetMinChannel():0;
97  const int maxtrack = dev?dev->GetMaxTrack():maxint;
98  const int mintrack = dev?dev->GetMinTrack():0;
99  if (!route) {
100  panel->SetFromChannel(minchannel, minchannel, maxchannel);
101  panel->SetToChannel(maxchannel, minchannel, maxchannel);
102  panel->SetFromTrack(mintrack, mintrack, maxtrack);
103  panel->SetToTrack(maxtrack, mintrack, maxtrack);
104  panel->SetRouteType(RTall);
105  return panel;
106  }
107  panel->SetFromChannel(route->GetInputFrom(), minchannel, maxchannel);
108  panel->SetToChannel(route->GetInputTo(), minchannel, maxchannel);
109  panel->SetFromTrack(route->GetInputFrom(), mintrack, maxtrack);
110  panel->SetToTrack(route->GetInputTo(), mintrack, maxtrack);
111  panel->SetRouteType(route->GetType());
112  return panel;
113  }

129  void OutputDevDlg::UpdateLayout(DevType type)
130  {
131  DEBUGLOG (other, "type: %d" ,type);
132  if (type == DTNotSet) {
133  DEBUGLOG (other, "Type not set" );
134  if (FindType (type) == wxNOT_FOUND)
135  DeviceChoice->Insert (_ ("Choose device type"),
136  0,
137  new TypeData (type));
138  } else {
139  int notset = FindType (DTNotSet);
140  if (notset != wxNOT_FOUND) {
141  DeviceChoice->Delete (notset);
142  }
143 
144  if (type == DTUnknown) {
145  if (FindType (type) == wxNOT_FOUND)
146  DeviceChoice->Insert (_ ("Unknown device type"),
147  0,
148  new TypeData (type));
149  }
150  }
151  int Type = FindType (type);
152  DeviceChoice -> SetSelection (Type);
153 
154  DEBUGLOG (other, "found Number %d (wxNOT_FOUND=%d)" ,type,wxNOT_FOUND);
155  wxSizer * sizer = GetSizer();
156 
157  DEBUGLOG (other, "DTMidiPort=%d" ,DTMidiPort);
158  sizer->Show(PortBox, type == DTMidiPort, true);
159  DEBUGLOG (other, "DTMidiFile=%d" ,DTMidiFile);
160  sizer->Show(MidiFileBox, (type == DTMidiFile), true);
161  DEBUGLOG (other, "DTGis=%d" ,DTGis);
162  sizer->Show(GuidoFileBox, (type == DTGis) , true);
163 
164  // We need Layout here, since otherwise the output boxex are not
165  // shown in certain circumstances
166  //CenterOnScreen();
167  Layout();
168  GetSizer()->SetSizeHints(this);
169  Fit();
170  }

192  int OutputDevDlg::FindType (DevType t)
193  {
194  TypeData * Data;
195  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < DeviceChoice->GetCount(); i++) {
196  DEBUGLOG (other, ("Choice #%d of %d"),i, DeviceChoice->GetCount());
197  Data = (TypeData *)DeviceChoice->GetClientObject(i);
198  if (Data) {
199  if (*Data == t) return i;
200  }
201  }
202  return wxNOT_FOUND;
203  }
204 }

virtual

transfers the configuration data of an input filter from a dialog panel to the route object Filter data is currently stored in some variables of the route class.

These varibles are reused for several purposes. depending on the corresponding input device..

This function reads data from an input filter panel of the route dialog and stores them in the appropriate variables as they are inerpred by a MIDI file input device class.
